{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c85e54f-4220-42c5-aba9-07d7f4685bd8","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n   \n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.5.0\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\nKey notes:\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces the VSTest runner and plugs xUnit into Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- Your existing `xunit` 2.9.3 package stays as-is.\n- You can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since MTP makes test projects executable.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4faa6076-0098-4623-8aae-31cc7cfb0a09","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest runner to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":352,"requestId":"0430:1C7D40:1E4433F:220E09D:69E81953"},"id":"832d22bc-810d-4066-8227-7e9b3a3919ef","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:02.698Z","parentId":"b6f60195-1b5b-4878-bae3-8bd6bedc9c6d"}
